THE RISK:
{
 "id": "large-operator-channel-forecloses-to-odm",
 "title": "The chosen first buyer — large operators — is migrating PDU procurement into ODM whole-rack deals, moving the decision to a channel the venture doesn't sell through",
 "narrative": "The venture's stated Year-1 route is selling to large operators, and cust.operator-large carries the biggest buyer weight (0.40) — justified in the ledger by hyperscale+colo being ~68% of capacity and large operators 'buying direct'. But direct purchase of discrete PDUs is exactly what large operators are unwinding: AI-density capacity is procured as integrated racks from ODM/rack integrators, where power distribution (shelf or PDU) is a BOM line the integrator sources under multi-year white-label agreements with incumbents. The demand doesn't shrink on paper — it relocates from cust.operator-large (where the venture has a channel plan) into cust.oem (where it has none), and BOM slots there are locked by Schneider/Vertiv/Eaton-class relationships years ahead. For a pre-launch entrant, a slice that moves to a foreclosed channel is functionally not addressable, whatever the buyer-mix pie chart says.",
 "category": "competitive",
 "targetNodes": [
  "cust.operator-large"
 ],
 "mechanism": [
  {
   "step": "trigger",
   "text": "The venture's primary Year-1 buyer is large operators, whose capacity base (hyperscale 48% + colo 20% of worldwide capacity per Synergy end-2025) underpins the 0.40 weight — and whose new AI-density capacity is procured as ODM-integrated racks rather than component PDUs",
   "refs": [
    "profile:Who is the primary buyer you'll sell through first?",
    "digest:seg-mix#c0",
    "digest:seg-mix#c1",
    "ledger:cust.operator-large"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "propagation",
   "text": "When rack power becomes an integrator BOM line, vendor selection shifts to white-label/OEM agreements dominated by the named incumbent set (Schneider at 15.8% plus a 5–7-vendor co-equal leader group per multiple reports); a pre-launch entrant with no ODM qualification cannot contest these slots inside 12 months",
   "refs": [
    "digest:cr3-vendors#c0",
    "digest:cr3-vendors#c6",
    "digest:cr3-vendors#c7",
    "ledger:cust.oem"
   ]
  },
  {
   "step": "model-impact",
   "text": "cust.operator-large's 0.40 is a needs-source internal estimate resting on one misused company-level order stat with zero published channel data; if a material fraction of large-operator PDU spend flows through integrator channels, the direct-sale pool the venture's entire Year-1 motion targets is overstated — YAM's obtainable assumption is applied to a pool that partly is not there",
   "refs": [
    "ledger:cust.operator-large",
    "ledger:cust.oem",
    "ledger:obtainableFactor"
   ]
  }
 ],
 "whyMissable": "The buyer-mix nodes are flagged 'needs-source', so the team's instinct is to validate the percentages via interviews — checking whether 0.40 is the right number. The risk isn't the number; it's that the category boundary between 'operator buys direct' and 'operator buys a rack' is moving during the entry window, so even a correctly-measured 2025 split is wrong by the time the pipeline matures.",
 "expectedObviousness": "low",
 "falsifier": "Procurement documentation from 2–3 large CE operators showing intelligent rack PDUs still tendered as a discrete direct-purchase category (separate RFQ line, operator-selected vendor) for their 2026–27 capacity additions, including AI-density halls.",
 "likelihood": {
  "value": 0.4,
  "rationale": "Integrated-rack procurement is documented for hyperscale AI deployments and the buyer-mix nodes have no evidential floor to resist the shift; however, European colo operators still run discrete PDU RFQs for standard halls, and the pace of channel migration within a 12-month window is genuinely uncertain. [evidence revision: Strong corroboration of the ODM-integrated-rack procurement mechanism and incumbent lock-in of power BOM slots raises confidence in the relocation thesis. However, the falsifying evidence shows PDUs still appear as procured line items (even if bundled into rack infrastructure) and that discrete power-distribution bids to operators persist in Europe, so the channel migration is real but not total within 12 months. Net modest upward revision from 0.35 to 0.40.]",
  "basis": "evidence",
  "revisedFrom": 0.35
 },
 "perturbation": [
  {
   "nodeId": "cust.operator-large",
   "op": "set",
   "value": 0.28,
   "note": "Portion of large-operator PDU spend relocates into integrator BOMs foreclosed to a new entrant — absolute shrink of the directly-winnable pool, below the ledger's 0.33 band floor"
  }
 ],
 "indicators": [
  {
   "signal": "Procurement structure in large-operator capacity programs (discrete PDU RFQs vs integrated rack packages)",
   "where": "TED (EU tender platform) for operator framework agreements; Equinix/Digital Realty/NTT procurement supplier-onboarding portals and capex call commentary",
   "threshold": "A major CE operator consolidating rack power into an integrated-rack or fit-out-contractor package for the first time",
   "updates": "increases"
  },
  {
   "signal": "ODM/integrator rack-scale revenue and PDU white-label announcements",
   "where": "OCP Global Summit sponsor/deployment talks; Foxconn/Quanta/Wiwynn investor updates on rack-scale system revenue; Legrand/Vertiv OEM-agreement press releases",
   "threshold": "Rack-scale integrated systems revenue at major ODMs growing >30% YoY with named European deployments",
   "updates": "increases"
  }
 ],
 "mitigations": [
  {
   "action": "Run the 3 planned CE operator/distributor interviews with an explicit procurement-structure module: what share of 2026-27 PDU spend is discrete RFQ vs integrator BOM, and who signs off the vendor",
   "type": "information",
   "voiNodeId": "cust.operator-large",
   "note": "Upgrades the ledger's existing promotion path from 'validate the split' to 'validate the split and its direction of travel'"
  },
  {
   "action": "Open a parallel OEM/integrator qualification track (design-in with one rack integrator serving CE colo builds) so the relocating demand remains reachable",
   "type": "strategic",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": "Hedges the Year-1 direct motion; cust.oem is 0.22 of the buyer mix and currently has no channel plan against it"
  },
  {
   "action": "Negotiate evaluation MOUs with 2 large operators that name the venture's PDU as an approved alternate in their fit-out contractor specs",
   "type": "contractual",
   "voiNodeId": null,
   "note": "Keeps the venture spec-listed even where purchasing is delegated to integrators"
  }
 ],
 "evidenceStatus": "corroborated",
 "evidence": [
  {
   "title": "Schneider Electric and Foxconn announce strategic collaboration to accelerate next-generation AI data centers",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "Schneider Electric / GlobeNewswire",
   "date": "2026-06-15",
   "excerpt": "brings together Foxconn’s unmatched expertise in advanced compute platforms, AI rack integration, and global manufacturing with Schneider Electric’s leadership in power systems... to deliver integrated, ready-to-deploy solutions",
   "url": "https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/06/15/3311506/0/en/Schneider-Electric-and-Hon-Hai-Technology-Group-Foxconn-announce-strategic-collaboration-to-accelerate-next-generation-AI-data-centers.html",
   "attached": true
  },
  {
   "title": "Wiwynn: The Heavy Metal Behind AI",
   "sourceType": "analyst-estimate",
   "publisher": "Silba Deep Dives",
   "date": "2026-01-31",
   "excerpt": "The hyperscalers... had stopped shopping for branded boxes. They wanted stripped-down designs, tuned to their specific workloads and priced without the markup",
   "url": "https://silbadeepdives.substack.com/p/6669-wiwynn-the-heavy-metal-behind",
   "attached": true
  },
  {
   "title": "Jarvis Ki Inferenz tender — Rack Infrastructure including PDU and CDU",
   "sourceType": "industry-report",
   "publisher": "Forschungszentrum Jülich / GlobalTenders",
   "date": "2026-07-01",
   "excerpt": "Rack Infrastructure, Including Power Distribution Units (Pdu) And Cooling Distribution Units (Cdu) Optimized For The Offered It Equipment",
   "url": "https://www.globaltenders.com/tender-detail/jarvis-eine-zentrale-plattform-f%C3%BCr-ki-infer-b3IRfCnbzDpiNXn3",
   "attached": true
  }
 ],
 "stances": [
  {
   "url": "https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/06/15/3311506/0/en/Schneider-Electric-and-Hon-Hai-Technology-Group-Foxconn-announce-strategic-collaboration-to-accelerate-next-generation-AI-data-centers.html",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "This collaboration brings together Foxconn’s unmatched expertise in advanced compute platforms, AI rack integration, and global manufacturing with Schneider Electric’s leadership in power systems, cooling, and energy management. Together, the companies aim to deliver integrated, ready-to-deploy solutions"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://nvidianews.nvidia.com/news/nvidia-releases-vera-rubin-dsx-ai-factory-reference-design-and-omniverse-dsx-digital-twin-blueprint-with-broad-industry-support",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "Industry leaders Cadence, Dassault Systèmes, Eaton, Jacobs, NScale, Phaidra, Procore Technologies, PTC, Schneider Electric, Siemens, Switch, Trane Technologies and Vertiv are contributing to the DSX architecture and blueprint by integrating platforms"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://silbadeepdives.substack.com/p/6669-wiwynn-the-heavy-metal-behind",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "The hyperscalers, those operating mega data centres rather than enterprise server rooms, had stopped shopping for branded boxes. They wanted stripped-down designs, tuned to their specific workloads"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://techblog.comsoc.org/2025/09/01/hyperscaler-compute-server-in-house-designs-with-odm-partners/",
   "stance": "supports",
   "quote": "use a mix of custom in‑house designs and ODM (Original Design Manufacturer) ‑ built hardware"
  },
  {
   "url": "https://www.globaltenders.com/tender-detail/jarvis-eine-zentrale-plattform-f%C3%BCr-ki-infer-b3IRfCnbzDpiNXn3",
   "stance": "contradicts",
   "quote": "Acquisition Of Ai Inference It Equipment Including Hardware And Mandatory Software.• Rack Infrastructure, Including Power Distribution Units (Pdu) And Cooling Distribution Units (Cdu) Optimized For The Offered It Equipment."
  },
  {
   "url": "https://en.wedoany.com/shortnews/152425.html",
   "stance": "contradicts",
   "quote": "had successfully won the bid for the high and low voltage cabinet equipment supply project for DayOne, a global data center operator, in its hyperscale data center located in Lahti, Finland"
  }
 ]
}

